UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12324
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract We examine a dynamic, two-sided, one-to-one matching market where agents on both sides interact over a period of time. We define and identify sufficient conditions for the existence of a dynamically stable matching, which may require revisions to initial assignments. A generalization of the deferred acceptance algorithm can identify dynamically stable outcomes in a large class of economies, including cases with intertemporal preference complementarities. We relate our analysis to market unraveling and to common market design applications, including the medical residency match.
ER  - 

